text.section:
"Concurrent review" means daily rounds by a licensed nurse which include:
Appraisal and observation of each resident by the licensed nurse to determine any change in the resident's physical or mental status; and
If there is a change in the resident's physical or mental status, an evaluation by the licensed nurse of:
The resident's medications;
Laboratory values relating to the resident;
Clinical data relating to the resident, including the resident's:
Hydration and nutritional need;
Skin integrity;
Noted weight changes; and
Appetite;
Injuries sustained by the resident that result from accident or incidents involving the resident; and
Any other relevant parameters affecting or reflecting the resident's physical and mental status.
